Added values for memory usage and TCP buffer usage

Note that this value corresponds to the number of users active in each time slice of 1/20th of a second, and not to the number of users having open connections.

dfl210PipeCurrentPps.name: dfl210PipeCurrentPps

dfl210PipeDelayedPackets.name: dfl210PipeDelayedPackets
dfl210PipeDelayedPackets.description: The number of times packets have been delayed as a result of a pipe, or pipe user having used up its allotted bandwidth. Note that one single packet may be delayed several times; if a pipe is really full, this count may exceed the number of packets actually passing through the pipe.

dfl210PipeDropedPackets.name: dfl210PipeDropedPackets
dfl210PipeDropedPackets.description: The number of packets dropped by a pipe. Packets are dropped when CorePlus is running out of packet buffers. This occurs when excessive amounts of packets need to be queued for later delivery. The packet dropped is always the one that has been queued the longest time globally, which means that the connection suffering from packet loss will be the one most overloading the system.

dfl210PipePrecTable.name: dfl210PipePrecTable
dfl210PipePrecTable.description: There is a one to many relation between a pipe and its precedences. The number of precedences is a instance attribute of each pipe. This table extends the pipes table in order to express the relation between a pipe and the respective precedences.

dfl210PipePrecEntry.name: dfl210PipePrecEntry
dfl210PipePrecEntry.description: An entry of the table of pipe pecedences. These table entries are chracterized by been indexed by two values. The first index the same as the pipe index of the corresponding row in table of pipes and the second index is the index of the set of precedences of the corresponding pipe.

dfl210PipePrecIndex.name: dfl210PipePrecIndex
dfl210PipePrecIndex.description: Index of a precedence of a specific pipe. This is the second index of the entries of pipe precedence table described by object dfl210PipePrecEntry.

dfl210PipePrecBps.name: dfl210PipePrecBps
dfl210PipePrecBps.description: The current throughput of the pipe, in bits per second, with the corresponding precedence.

dfl210PipePrecTotalPps.name: dfl210PipePrecTotalPps
dfl210PipePrecTotalPps.description: The current throughput of the pipe precedence, in packets per second.

dfl210PipePrecReservedBps.name: dfl210PipePrecReservedBps

dfl210PipePrecDynUsrLimBps.name: dfl210PipePrecDynUsrLimBps
dfl210PipePrecDynUsrLimBps.description: The current precedence bandwidth limit per user of the pipe.

dfl210PipePrecDelayedPackets.name: dfl210PipePrecDelayedPackets
dfl210PipePrecDelayedPackets.description: The number of times packets have been delayed as a result of a precedence, or pipe user having used up its allotted bandwidth. Note that one single packet may be delayed several times; if a pipe is really full, this count may exceed the number of packets of this precedence actually passing through the pipe.
